        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Complaint Details</div><p><strong>Complainant:</strong> European Consumer Shield (NGO)<br><strong>Representative:</strong> Clara Vance</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Background</div><p>Over the past three months, we have received 4,200 identical complaints regarding LuminaCart. Consumers report entering the site to browse and suddenly making massive, uncharacteristic purchases—often luxury items they cannot afford. Many describe a "trance-like" compulsion. Several consumers have fallen into severe financial debt, defaulting on rent to pay off LuminaCart credit lines. The site features a blue colour scheme and servers hosted in Ireland.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Whistleblower Evidence</div><p>Dr. Aris Thorne, a former data scientist at LuminaCart, provided us with internal logs. He claims the site uses an AI system to generate imperceptible audio-visual cues. While we acknowledge the pop-up banners are annoying, Dr. Thorne stresses the real issue is what users cannot see or hear.</p></div>'
