        id: 'ev2-technical-document',
        type: 'technical-document',
        title: 'Vulnerability Targeting Engine — Design Specs',
        date: 'February 10, 2027',
        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">1. System Architecture</div><p>The Vulnerability Targeting Engine (VTE) uses machine learning to predict acute liquidity crises in real-time. It processes linked bank account telemetry to generate a dynamic "Desperation Score" (1-100) for each user.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">2. Trigger Parameters</div><p>The VTE initiates high-friction push notifications offering instant credit when the following conditions are met:</p><p>\u2022 Account balance drops below \u20AC50.<br>\u2022 A historical fixed expense (e.g., rent, utilities) is due within 48 hours.<br>\u2022 The user\'s recent transaction history shows "stress indicators" (e.g., purchases at discount stores, denied card transactions).</p></div><div class="doc-highlight"><strong>Algorithm Goal:</strong> The system aims to maximize the loan acceptance rate. Internal testing confirms that presenting the offer during a period of peak financial anxiety (Desperation Score > 85) increases the likelihood of the user accepting the maximum APR tier by 410% compared to offering the loan during a period of financial stability.</div>'
