        content: '<div class="doc-section"><p><strong>From:</strong> Chief Compliance Officer<br><strong>To:</strong> VP of Product, CrediCatch<br><strong>Subject:</strong> Legal Risk Assessment: VTE</p><hr><p>I am raising a formal concern regarding the Vulnerability Targeting Engine. The EU AI Act expressly prohibits using AI to exploit people\'s economic situations. Deliberately timing loans to hit when someone is broke and desperate seems like a clear violation.</p><hr><p><strong>From:</strong> VP of Product<br><strong>To:</strong> Chief Compliance Officer<br><strong>Subject:</strong> RE: Legal Risk Assessment: VTE</p><p>We are covered. We had legal draft an ironclad GDPR consent banner. When they sign up, they explicitly consent to us profiling their financial data to provide "personalized credit offers." As long as we have GDPR consent, we can use their data however we want to optimize conversions. We aren\'t doing anything illegal, we are just giving them credit when they need it most.</p></div>'
