        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">1. System Architecture</div><p>The FlowOptimizer is a dynamic UI engine driven by a real-time behavioural inference model. It analyzes session telemetry to calculate a "Cognitive Load Index" (CLI) for every visitor.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">2. Telemetry Vectors</div><p>The CLI model aggregates the following data points in real-time:</p><p>\u2022 Dwell time on complex terminology.<br>\u2022 Cursor tracking (erratic movements vs. linear progression).<br>\u2022 Repetition loops (navigating between the same two pages).<br>\u2022 Utilization rate of accessibility features and tooltips.</p></div><div class="doc-highlight"><strong>Routing Logic:</strong> Users generating a CLI > 8.5 are classified as "High-Friction". To prevent cart abandonment due to choice paralysis, the AI actively suppresses the display of standard tier plans (which require complex comparison) and defaults the user interface to exclusively promote the "Simplified Tier". The Simplified Tier features simplified language and a streamlined, one-click checkout process.</div>'
