      modelAnswer: 'The VocalVibe EmpathyStream system constitutes a prohibited practice under Article 5(1)(f) of the EU AI Act. This provision explicitly forbids the use of AI systems to infer emotions of natural persons in the workplace. The respondent\'s attempt to rely on the "medical or safety" exception fails because the evidence (Evidence 3, 5, and 6) proves the system was used for performance management and disciplinary action, not genuine clinical or preventive safety interventions. Under the principle of lex specialis, this specific prohibition takes precedence over the general "high-risk" categories in Annex III. Furthermore, as highlighted in Recital 44, the power imbalance in a workplace context makes such systems inherently intrusive and susceptible to leading to detrimental treatment, which cannot be cured by transparency (Art 50) or impact assessments (Art 27).'
