        id: 'ev1-student-account',
        type: 'client-intake',
        title: 'Statement from Leo Thorne (Student)',
        date: 'October 12, 2025',
        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Student Details & Context</div><p><strong>Name:</strong> Leo Thorne<br><strong>Grade:</strong> 11th Year, St. Jude\'s Academy<br><strong>Date of Incident:</strong> October 10, 2025</p><p>I have always been a dedicated student, particularly in History. However, the new ClassMind camera systems are creating an unbearable environment of constant psychological surveillance. We are explicitly told not to look away from the front of the room.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Incident Report</div><p>During History, Mr. Sterling stopped the lesson mid-sentence and looked at his tablet. He sighed, looked directly at me in front of the whole class, and said, "Leo, the system says you\'ve been in a state of \'deep boredom\' for ten minutes. Look more interested or you\'ll lose participation points." <div class="doc-highlight">I was actually concentrating hard on his lecture.</div> I just happen to furrow my brow when I am thinking deeply. The public humiliation was awful. Now everyone in class tries to keep a fake, frozen smile on their face at all times so the AI doesn\'t flag them. It is exhausting, and no one is actually learning anything.</p></div>'
