        type: 'technical-document',
        title: 'ClassMind AI: Teacher Dashboard Guide',
        date: 'August 2025',
        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Hardware and Data Capture</div><p>The ClassMind AI framework requires the installation of ultra-high-definition optical sensors at the front of the instructional space. These cameras capture live, continuous video feeds of the student body, isolating individual faces even in poor lighting or high-density seating arrangements. Video streams are processed locally via edge-computing nodes before being aggregated.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Emotional State Inference</div><p>Through proprietary neural networks trained on millions of adolescent expressions, the ClassMind algorithm utilizes biometric templates to <div class="doc-highlight">infer the underlying emotional and cognitive states</div> of students. By mapping 64 specific facial landmarks—including pupil dilation, eyebrow furrowing, and lip tension—the system categorizes student sentiment into four primary quadrants: Engagement, Confusion, Frustration, and Apathy. This data is refreshed every 5 seconds to provide teachers with a live, color-coded heat map of classroom sentiment on their synchronized tablets, enabling real-time pedagogical interventions.</p></div>'
