        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Confidential Legal Memo</div><p><strong>From:</strong> J. Miller (External Legal Counsel, Tech Law Partners)<br><strong>To:</strong> Principal Silas Vance<br><strong>Subject:</strong> Legal Liabilities of ClassMind Deployment</p><hr><p>Silas, following our consultation, I must formally document my severe concerns about your plans regarding Article 5(1)(f) of the AI Act. The statutory prohibition on emotion recognition in educational institutions is absolute and interpreted quite broadly by regulators.</p><p>You cannot simply rename the technology to bypass the law. <div class="doc-highlight">Labeling it \'engagement monitoring\' does not change the fact that the system infers emotional states from biometric data.</div> A semantic rebrand will not survive a regulatory audit. Unless we can definitively prove this deployment is strictly for a medical reason (e.g., monitoring a student with a specific diagnosed neurological condition prescribed by a physician), we are at high risk of a total operational ban and substantial financial penalties. I strongly advise pausing this initiative.</p></div>'
