              judge_response: 'Counsel, Article 111 provides transitions for high-risk systems, but do these transitions apply to prohibited practices that represent an unacceptable risk? Is there any "grace period" for a system that is fundamentally banned?',
              legal_reasoning: 'This is the trap. It misapplies transition periods (which exist for some parts of the Act) to \"Prohibited Practices.\" The AI Act generally requires prohibited practices to cease much sooner because they represent an unacceptable risk that cannot be \"transitioned\" into compliance.'
