        type: 'client-intake',
        title: 'Client Statement: Luka Kovac',
        date: 'October 15, 2025',
        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Personal Background</div><p>My name is Luka Kovac. I am a second-year engineering student at the State University. I work part-time at a local bakery to pay my tuition. I have never even had a parking ticket, let alone a criminal record.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Timeline of Harassment</div><p>But since September 1st, the police are everywhere I go. I have been stopped and searched five times in a single month while walking home from the library. During the most recent stop on October 12th, one officer told me I was \'in the system\' and that my profile suggests a 78% chance of involvement in \'property crime\' within the next year. <div class="doc-highlight">They asked me about my father\'s record from twenty years ago and why I live in a low-income housing block.</div> They even asked if my social media posts about "financial struggles" meant I was planning a theft. I am terrified to leave my apartment. I feel like a criminal before I\'ve even done anything, just because of where I live and who my family is.</p></div>'
