        date: 'December 4, 2025',
        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Secure Drop: Internal Data Leak</div><p>On December 2nd, the ECLU received an encrypted data cache from a whistleblower formerly employed as a senior systems architect at Aura Analytics. The cache included multiple high-resolution screenshots of the live Prism-AI administrative dashboard, taken remotely from a deployment at the Grand Galleria Mall.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Dashboard Observations</div><p>The system displays a live 4K video feed of the main mall corridor with neon bounding boxes tracking moving faces. <div class="doc-highlight">Each box is dynamically tagged with a probability score for \'Ethnic Heritage\' and \'Political Orientation.\'</div> The labeling is shockingly blunt. One screenshot clearly shows a diverse group of university students labeled as \'Audience Segment: Progressive/Gen-Z\' based on their combined facial expressions and speech patterns recorded at the kiosk. Even more concerning, individual shoppers walking alone are tagged with explicit inferences such as \'Likely Muslim\' and \'Conservative Traditionalist\', instantly triggering targeted digital advertisements on the adjacent kiosk screens as they pass by.</p></div>'
