        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Prism-AI Operational Manual (v2.1)</div><p><strong>Section:</strong> 3.2 Categorisation Protocols & Data Handling</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Real-Time Processing</div><p>The Prism-AI system is explicitly designed to segment the public in order to optimize mall revenue and maximize targeted advertising yields. <div class="doc-highlight">The categorisation of natural persons occurs instantly upon detection.</div> Processing is handled locally on the kiosk\'s internal GPU to ensure latency remains under 300 milliseconds. No human oversight is required or possible during the inference phase.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Data Retention</div><p>To comply with basic privacy standards, the system immediately purges the raw optical and acoustic data (video frames and audio clips) once the biometric template is processed. However, the resulting sensitive inferences—specifically tags for Race, Religion, and Politics—are attached to an anonymized tracking token. These inferred demographic profiles are stored on our central servers for 24 hours to analyze the broader traffic patterns, dwell times, and shopping habits of specific protected demographic groups across the retail property.</p></div>'
