      narrative: 'City General Hospital deployed \'DermScan AI\', a high-risk medical diagnostic tool designed to assist radiologists and dermatologists in identifying malignant melanomas. Your client, Amara Okoro, visited the clinic for a routine check of a suspicious mole on her shoulder. The AI analyzed the image and returned a \'Low Risk / Benign\' result. Six months later, the mole began to bleed. A manual biopsy revealed Stage III melanoma. An investigation by the Digital Health Watchdog discovered that DermScan AI was trained on a dataset where 92% of the images were from patients with Fitzpatrick Skin Types I and II (light skin). As Amara\'s legal counsel, you are suing the provider, SkinTech AI, for failing to meet the data governance and risk management requirements of the EU AI Act.',
      client: { name: 'Amara Okoro', role: 'Patient and Plaintiff' },
      respondent: { name: 'SkinTech AI Solutions', type: 'AI Provider' },
      setting: 'District Court for Civil Matters, Berlin, October 2025'
