        content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Email Thread: Beta Testing Feedback</div><p><strong>From:</strong> Tech Lead (ExamWatch Integration Team)<br><strong>To:</strong> Dean Arthur Sterling (Digital Learning)<br><strong>Date:</strong> February 15, 2025 14:10</p><p>Dean Sterling, we\'ve run the beta tests on the new proctoring software. We have two main concerns. First, the optical tracker struggles to maintain a lock on students in "busy" backgrounds or low-light shared rooms, which often triggers false \'absence\' flags.</p><p>Second, <div class="doc-highlight">we haven\'t specifically tested the model for accessibility compliance regarding involuntary tics</div> or other neuro-motor conditions. The vendor\'s dataset didn\'t include those edge cases. Should we delay the rollout until we can calibrate the software for the students in the Disability Support program?</p><hr><p><strong>From:</strong> Dean Arthur Sterling<br><strong>To:</strong> Tech Lead<br><strong>Date:</strong> February 16, 2025 08:30</p><p>No delay. The Provost wants this live for midterms. Given the launch date, we\'ll have to monitor these issues post-deployment. If a student has an issue, they can appeal it later. Push it to production.</p></div>'
