      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Deposition Excerpt: Dr. Leo Chen</div><p><strong>Witness:</strong> Dr. Leo Chen, Lead Developer, Edutech Solutions (Vendor for Gatekeeper AI)<br><strong>Date:</strong> June 10, 2025</p></div><div class="doc-section"><p>"When we pitched the system to Aalto-Strasbourg, the University specifically asked for maximum administrative efficiency. They wanted to eliminate the backlog of average applications. We gave them a model that correlates tens of thousands of data points simultaneously.</p><p>During development, we realized that building an interpretation layer—something that could explain the \'why\' behind a score—would degrade the model\'s processing speed by 40% and lower its overall predictive accuracy. <div class="doc-highlight">We knowingly sacrificed explainability for predictive accuracy.</div> If the AI finds a hidden, complex pattern in a student\'s extracurricular history that correlates with low graduation rates, it rejects them. We can\'t pull out the specific \'reason\' for the admissions office because it\'s a holistic, non-linear mathematical calculation occurring across millions of parameters. We told the University it was a black box, and they signed the contract anyway."</p></div>'
