            text: 'Your Honour, the AI Act only applies to systems that make \"final\" decisions. Since HireSmart AI only performs a \"first pass\" and then gives the resumes to HR, it is a low-risk system that falls under the transparency-only rules of Article 50. CloudScale has met these rules by putting a small disclaimer in the footer of its careers page. Because a human (Mr. Miller) technically reviews the logs once a week, the system is not high-risk and the data governance rules in Article 10 do not apply at all.',
            judge_response: 'Counsel, recruitment screening is explicitly listed as a high-risk category in Annex III, regardless of whether it is a \"first pass\" or a final decision. Your attempt to downgrade the risk category is legally incorrect.',
            legal_reasoning: 'Fundamental error. It wrongly claims that screening is not high-risk if it\'s a \"first pass\" and misrepresents the scope of Art 50 vs Art 10.'
