            id: 'arg1-weak',
            quality: 'weak',
            text: 'Your Honour, it is fundamentally unfair to have a computer decide your career in secret. The AI Act says that high-risk systems should be transparent so people know what is happening to them. The company\'s own analyst said he couldn\'t even explain the scores. This shows that the system is a \"black box\" that has no place in a modern office. If the company wants to use AI, they have to make sure it is human-centric and that every employee gets a full explanation of how they are being graded.',
            judge_response: 'I agree with the fairness concern, but please focus on the specific statutory requirement for the deployer to \"interpret the output\" under Article 13.',
            legal_reasoning: 'Correct in spirit but lacks statutory precision. It appeals to \"human-centric\" values rather than applying the specific legal test of Art 13.'
