            quality: 'wrong',
            text: 'Your Honour, the company has violated Article 10 of the AI Act regarding data and data governance. Because they did not use a representative dataset for the keystroke analysis, the system is biased against people who type slower. Under Article 10, all training data must be error-free and complete. Since Sarah is a great manager but a slow typer, the data used to train the system must have been defective. The remedy is to order the company to retrain the AI using a more diverse set of typing samples until the \"Agility\" score is accurate for everyone.',
            judge_response: 'Counsel, while data governance is important, the current argument is about transparency. Are you not conflating the quality of the data with the failure to inform the employees and interpret the results?',
            legal_reasoning: 'Fundamental error. It applies Article 10 (Data Governance) to a case centered on Transparency (Art 13/50). It also wrongly claims data must be \"error-free\" (the Act says \"to the best extent possible\").'
