            quality: 'weak',
            text: 'Your Honour, you can\'t just hide a biometric system and call it \"monitoring.\" The AI Act says that people have a right to know when they are being exposed to this kind of technology. The handbook (Evidence 6) is too vague because it doesn\'t mention AI or keystrokes at all. The employees should have been told that their typing was being turned into a score. By keeping it a secret, the company treated their staff like lab rats instead of people, and that is a clear violation of the transparency rules that are supposed to protect us.',
