            judge_response: 'Counsel, Article 2 does not provide a general \"secrecy\" exemption that allows you to bypass the mandatory transparency obligations of Article 50. The AI Act is absolutely a transparency law.',
            legal_reasoning: 'Fundamental error. It invents a \"secrecy exception\" in Article 2 and wrongly claims the AI Act doesn\'t prioritize transparency, which is a core pillar of the Regulation.'
