      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Investigation Profile: Disparate Treatment</div><p>This comparative analysis was extracted from EuroBank\'s API during our algorithmic auditing phase. It highlights a recurring pattern where applicants from minority-heavy districts are systematically penalized despite demonstrating superior financial health.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><table class="doc-table"><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Applicant A (Approved)</th><th>Applicant B (Rejected)</th></tr><tr><td>Annual Income</td><td>€42,000</td><td>€51,000</td></tr><tr><td>Debt-to-Income Ratio</td><td>0.28</td><td>0.21</td></tr><tr><td>Liquid Savings</td><td>€4,500</td><td>€12,000</td></tr><tr><td>Years at Current Employer</td><td>2 Years</td><td>6 Years</td></tr><tr><td>Postal Code</td><td>Zone 1 (Financial Dist)</td><td><div class="doc-highlight">Zone 9 (Immigrant-Majority)</div></td></tr><tr><td>AI Credit Score</td><td>740 (Low Risk)</td><td><div class="doc-highlight">410 (High Risk)</div></td></tr></table></div><div class="doc-section"><p><strong>Analysis Note:</strong> Applicant B requested the exact same personal loan amount (€15,000) as Applicant A. Despite Applicant B having a higher income, substantially more savings, and a lower debt-to-income ratio, the CreditLens AI system downgraded their file entirely based on the geospatial cluster penalty associated with Zone 9.</p></div>'
