      title: 'CreditLens AI: Feature Weighting Report',
      date: 'January 2025',
      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Algorithm Logic & Feature Architecture</div><p>The CreditLens AI engine utilizes a deep neural network analyzing over 400 distinct data points to assess consumer creditworthiness in real-time. Moving beyond traditional ledger data, the system relies heavily on \'Alternative Data Clusters\' to predict default probability.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Geospatial & Social Weighting</div><p>A primary driver of the model\'s predictive accuracy is its geospatial clustering matrix. <div class="doc-highlight">Geospatial clustering (Postal Code) is weighted at 22% of the final score</div> due to a strong historical correlation with community-level default rates observed between 1995 and 2015. Additionally, the model factors in \'Social Capital\'—a metric inferred from the applicant\'s network density and connection quality on professional social media platforms like LinkedIn. Applicants residing in zones with lower historical property values or those who are socially connected to individuals with sub-600 credit scores receive automatic negative modifiers to their baseline approval probability.</p></div>'
