            judge_response: 'Transparency is important, but does a better disclosure notice fix a system that is fundamentally biased in its core weights? If the system is discriminatory under Article 10, does \"telling people\" make it lawful?',
            legal_reasoning: 'This is the trap. It identifies a real transparency issue (Art. 13), but in this case, the core violation is Art. 10 (data governance). A transparency notice does not cure a defective and biased dataset; it just documents the bias.'
