            text: 'Your Honour, the risk management plan is just a piece of paper. It says the system is neutral because it doesn\'t use the word \"Race,\" but everyone knows that postal codes are used to discriminate. The company\'s own developer told them it was redlining, but they kept it anyway. This shows that GLH was more interested in making money than in being fair to people in social regeneration zones. By ignoring the risk and using the neighborhood data, they broke the law and they should be held responsible.',
            judge_response: 'I agree that the \"blindness\" defense is weak, but please address the specific requirement in Article 9(2) regarding the mitigation of risks through design.',
