            quality: 'wrong',
            text: 'Your Honour, the AI Act only applies to systems that result in \"physical injury.\" Since being overcharged for insurance is a financial matter, the AI Act does not apply to this case. Furthermore, insurance premiums are governed by national contract law, and the AI Act cannot override a private company\'s right to set its own prices. The policyholder has no standing to bring this case because she has not suffered a physical harm as defined in Article 3 of the Regulation.',
            judge_response: 'Counsel, the AI Act explicitly protects against negative impacts on fundamental rights, including the right to non-discrimination. And it certainly applies to high-risk insurance systems. Your argument is entirely false.',
