    narrative: 'The Justice Department of the Northern Territory has deployed \'BailBound AI\', a high-risk system designed to predict the likelihood of a defendant committing a new crime while on bail. The system is trained on twenty years of local arrest and detention records. Your client, Sofia Rossi, is representing a young man from District 8, a neighborhood with a long history of over-policing. Despite having a clean record, he was flagged as \'High Risk\' by the AI. This flag led the judge to set a \u20AC50,000 bail he couldn\'t afford. While in detention, he missed a court check-in, which the AI then registered as a \'violation,\' further increasing his risk score. This case challenges the system on the grounds that it creates a discriminatory feedback loop and was trained on biased data that reflects systemic policing patterns rather than actual criminal risk.',
