            judge_response: 'The court is struck by the term \"administrative penalty.\" If the UI is designed to make the judge hesitate through fear of a report, it is not enabling oversight; it is obstructing it. Dr. Blackwood, why is the form CC\'d to the Appointments Commission?',
            legal_reasoning: 'This argument correctly identifies that the *design* of the oversight mechanism must enable, not hinder, the human. It uses Evidence 2 to show the UI was built to discourage overrides, violating Art 14(1) and (4e).'
