            text: 'Your Honour, the primary violation here is a failure of the Risk Management System under Article 9. The Ministry failed to identify \'Judicial Over-reliance\' as a foreseeable risk in its assessment. According to Article 9(2), the provider should have implemented technical mitigations, such as a \'Confidence Score\' that warns the judge when the data is uncertain. Because the Ministry did not follow the risk management hierarchy to reduce this risk through design, the system is non-compliant. The remedy is to suspend the system until a new Article 9 assessment is conducted and a human-centric interface is developed.',
            judge_response: 'Risk management is indeed a requirement. But if we are discussing the *actual* failure of the human to override the system in a specific case, is Article 14 not the more direct and specific provision? Does Article 9 fix the judge\'s current lack of discretion?',
