            judge_response: 'Is the problem the system\'s accuracy, or the way the human is pressured to interact with it? Even if the AI were 100% accurate on average, does Article 14 not still require the human to be able to override it for a specific exception?',
            legal_reasoning: 'This is a plausible error. Art 15 (Accuracy) is a separate requirement. A system could be very accurate but still violate Art 14 if it makes human intervention too difficult. This tests the student\'s ability to isolate the oversight failure from technical performance.'
