          quality: 'wrong',
          text: 'Your Honour, the National Power Grid is exempt from the AI Act under Article 2(3) regarding national security. The power grid is a matter of national security, and the AI system used to manage it is therefore not subject to the standard high-risk rules. Furthermore, the AI Act only protects \"consumers\" as individuals, and since the blackout affected an entire region, it is a collective matter that should be handled under energy law rather than the AI Act. NPG is free to manage its risks however it sees fit to protect the stability of the state.',
          judge_response: 'Counsel, \"National Security\" is not a magic word that exempts critical infrastructure from the safety rules of the AI Act. Annex III explicitly includes critical infrastructure. And the Act certainly protects people from collective infrastructure failures.',
          legal_reasoning: 'Fundamental error. It invents a "national security" exemption that does not apply to civilian critical infrastructure and wrongly claims the Act only applies to individual consumer harms.'
