            quality: 'weak',
            text: 'Your Honour, you can\'t just say manipulation isn\'t a risk. The email from the CEO (Evidence 3) shows they knew they were tricking people and they didn\'t care. The AI Act says you have to manage all risks, and tricking people into voting for someone is the biggest risk there is for a democracy. By not doing a real assessment, they broke the law and put the whole election in danger. The court should make them stop using the system until they can prove it doesn\'t manipulate anyone\'s brain with fear or anger.',
            judge_response: 'I agree that the risk is significant, but please address the specific requirement in Article 9 regarding the identification of foreseeable risks to fundamental rights.',
            legal_reasoning: 'Correct in spirit but lacks statutory precision. It fails to cite the specific link between Annex III, point 8 and the Article 9 risk management duty.'
