            text: 'Your Honour, Article 9 only applies to AI systems that are \"placed on the market.\" Since DemocracyLabs is using VoterPulse AI as an internal service for a specific client, it is considered \"research and development\" and is exempt from the risk management rules. Furthermore, under Article 2(6), any AI used for the purpose of promoting \"European Values\" like democracy is automatically exempt from the high-risk rules. Since the Unity Party is a democratic party, their use of AI is a protected activity that the AI Act was never intended to regulate or restrict.',
            judge_response: 'Counsel, you are misstating the law. High-risk systems \"put into service\" for electoral influence are fully covered, and there is no \"European Values\" exemption from safety rules. Your argument is legally incoherent.',
            legal_reasoning: 'Fundamental error. It invents an "internal service" exemption and a "European Values" exemption, both of which are false under the AI Act.'
