            text: 'Your Honour, the "obviousness" defense is refuted by the provider\'s own technical design. Article 50(1) requires systems to be designed and developed so that the person is informed. Evidence 2 and 6 prove that MindMend did the exact opposite: they fine-tuned the AI with "artificial typing delays," "intentional typos," and instructions to "avoid all mentions of being an AI." When a provider spends months of engineering effort to manufacture a human-identical persona and explicitly deflect questions about its nature, they cannot claim the AI nature was "obvious." This is "Deception by Design," a willful breach of the development standards of the Act.',
