      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Journalism Ethics Board: Investigation Summary</div><p>Following a preliminary audit of digital news publishers, we have identified a severe, systematic breach of transparency protocols at Europress Media Group.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Statement of Facts</div><p>Between March and July 2025, Europress published approximately 4,200 articles primarily generated by a large language model (NewsWire AI). <div class="doc-highlight">None of these articles carried a disclosure label, watermark, or footnote indicating algorithmic generation.</div> Readers reasonably believed they were consuming human-authored, verified financial and geopolitical analysis.</p><p>The deception culminated on July 10th, when a market-moving report on the European Central Bank\'s (ECB) interest rate policy and a major bank\'s liquidity was published. The article contained several "AI hallucinations" (fabricated quotes attributed to an ECB official), causing a brief but severe panic in regional bond markets. Forensic text analysis confirmed the article was 98% identical to a raw draft generated by NewsWire AI, yet it was published under the trusted byline of their Chief Economics Editor, who was later revealed to be on vacation at the time of publication.</p></div>'
