      date: 'July 2025',
      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Content Management System (CMS) Raw Export</div><p><strong>Query:</strong> Time-to-Publish variance for AI-Generated Drafts (July 8 - July 12)</p></div><div class="doc-section"><table class="doc-table"><tr><th>Article ID / Category</th><th>AI Generation Completed At</th><th>Human "Review Started" (File Opened)</th><th>"Published" (Sent to Live Server)</th></tr><tr><td>FIN-992 (Banking)</td><td>14:02:10</td><td>14:02:15</td><td><div class="doc-highlight">14:02:45 (Duration: 30s)</div></td></tr><tr><td>SPT-441 (Football)</td><td>15:10:05</td><td>15:10:20</td><td>15:10:55 (Duration: 35s)</td></tr><tr><td>POL-112 (ECB Rates)</td><td>09:14:00</td><td>09:14:10</td><td>09:14:48 (Duration: 38s)</td></tr><tr><td>FIN-995 (Earnings)</td><td>11:45:00</td><td>11:45:15</td><td>11:45:40 (Duration: 25s)</td></tr></table></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Forensic Analysis</div><p>An audit of 500 randomly selected articles flagged as "AI-Drafted" reveals that the average time elapsed between a human editor opening the file ("Review Started") and authorizing it for public release ("Published") is exactly 34 seconds. Given the average article length of 800 words, this timeframe is physically insufficient for substantive fact-checking, source verification, or meaningful editorial oversight.</p></div>'
