      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Independent Textual Forensics Report</div><p><strong>Methodology:</strong> A programmatic comparison of the raw, unedited text generated by NewsWire AI (extracted from internal servers) versus the final text published live on Europress.com under human bylines.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Comparison Metrics (Sample Size: 500 Articles)</div><ul><li>Average Textual Overlap (Identical strings): <div class="doc-highlight">96.4%</div></li><li>Substantive Editorial Changes (Altering facts, restructuring arguments, changing tone): 0.8%</li><li>Cosmetic Editorial Changes (Fixing punctuation, standardizing dates, bolding text): 2.8%</li></ul></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Conclusion</div><p>The forensic data definitively proves that the "human review" process at Europress is a procedural facade. The published articles are substantially and materially unchanged from the raw algorithmic output. The human interaction is limited almost entirely to formatting tweaks, meaning the AI is acting as the primary author, not an assistive editor.</p></div>'
