            text: 'Your Honour, the failure to red-team is a violation of the Quality Management System (QMS) requirements under Article 17. High-risk AI providers must have a QMS that includes procedures for pre-market testing and adversarial simulation. Because NovaCore failed to document their red-teaming results in their technical file, they have breached the administrative standards for trustworthy AI. The appropriate remedy is to fine the company under Article 99 for a documentation failure and order them to hire a \"Chief Safety Officer\" to oversee the implementation of the QMS for all future multimodal models.',
            judge_response: 'Counsel, you are once again applying High-Risk System rules (Art 17) to a GPAI Model. While both require testing, Article 55 is the *specific* provision for systemic risk models. Does a QMS documentation fine address the substantive failure to red-team a model of this power?',
            legal_reasoning: 'This is the trap. It misapplies High-Risk System obligations (Art 17/99) to a GPAI model provider. While GPAI providers have a QMS-like duty in Art 53, the specific red-teaming duty for systemic risk is Art 55. This tests the student\'s ability to stay within the GPAI legal framework.'
