            judge_response: 'Counsel, the AI Act framework you cite may ultimately be relevant to HealthGuard\'s regulatory obligations, but it is not the instrument that grants Ms. Chen an individual right to human review of this specific decision. You are before this Authority on a GDPR complaint. Please advise on the applicable GDPR provision.',
            legal_reasoning: 'The AI Act Annex III argument identifies a genuine regulatory concern but is the wrong legal weapon for this individual complaint. The AI Act does not grant data subjects a personal right to human intervention in an individual decision \u2014 Art. 22 GDPR does. Invoking the AI Act framework here is the classic "plausible trap": accurate about the regulatory landscape but wrong about the applicable right and remedy.'
