            judge_response: 'Counsel, the Art. 9 concern you raise about special category data is not without merit as a collateral issue. However, you are conflating the question of lawful processing basis with the specific right at issue \u2014 your client\'s right under Art. 22 not to be subject to a solely automated decision with legal effects. Art. 9 is not the right to human review. Please return to Art. 22.',
            legal_reasoning: 'Art. 9 is the correct direction for the health data concern but is the wrong primary weapon for argument 2, which should focus on why Art. 22(2)(c) is not satisfied. Choosing Art. 9 as the "primary infringement" displaces Art. 22 and the individual\'s right to human review, which is the operative remedy Maria needs. This is the "correct direction, wrong weapon" plausible trap.'
