      date: '2024-12-03',
      content: '<div class="doc-section"><p class="doc-section-title">Email Thread: RE: CreditMind Review Process \u2014 GDPR Art. 22 Exposure</p><p><strong>From:</strong> Ingrid Scholz, Chief Compliance Officer<br/><strong>To:</strong> Markus Dierks, Head of Credit Operations<br/><strong>Date:</strong> 3 December 2024, 10:22</p><p>"Markus \u2014 I have reviewed the CreditMind officer interface and I am formally flagging an Art. 22 compliance risk. The review screen shows no reasoning, no input breakdowns, and no documentation. <span class="doc-highlight">An officer confirming a recommendation they cannot interrogate is not \'human intervention\' within the meaning of GDPR Art. 22(3). The EDPB guidance is clear: a rubber-stamp process does not break the \'solely automated\' threshold.</span> We need a genuine review capability or we face significant enforcement risk."</p><hr/><p><strong>From:</strong> Markus Dierks<br/><strong>To:</strong> Ingrid Scholz<br/><strong>Date:</strong> 3 December 2024, 15:47</p><p><span class="doc-highlight">"Ingrid \u2014 A human being clicks the button. That is human review. Legal will document it as such. We process 200 applications per day \u2014 a genuine review process would destroy our turnaround time. The current model stays."</span></p></div>'
