      content: '<div class="doc-section"><p class="doc-section-title">Rejection Letter Sent to Jan Mueller \u2014 15 January 2025</p><p><em>Subject: Your EuroCredit Loan Application \u2014 Decision</em></p><p>"Dear Mr. Mueller, Following assessment of your application, we regret to inform you that your application does not meet our creditworthiness requirements. EuroCredit Bank AG is unable to approve your loan request at this time. For further assistance, please contact our customer helpline."</p><hr/><p class="doc-section-title">GDPR Art. 15(1)(h) Requirement (annotated for comparison):</p><p>Where automated decision-making including profiling is used, the controller must provide: <span class="doc-highlight">\u201CMeaningful information about the logic involved, as well as the significance and the envisaged consequences of such processing for the data subject.\u201D</span></p><p><strong>What the letter provides:</strong> Zero disclosure that an automated system made the decision. Zero explanation of any logic, weighting, or input factors. Zero mention of postcode as a factor. Zero information about the right to request human review or to contest the outcome. The letter is a single sentence of conclusory denial with a helpline number.</p></div>'
