        questionText: 'Isn\'t it true that CreditMind\'s predictive accuracy for default risk is demonstrably higher than human underwriters achieved historically, and that automating the process has actually reduced discriminatory outcomes compared to the subjective judgments human officers used to make?',
        category: 'risky',
        witnessResponse: 'Absolutely. Our model has been validated against five years of historical default data. It outperforms human judgment on every measurable accuracy metric. And because it applies criteria consistently, it is objectively fairer than a process where individual officers apply their own biases. Automation here serves the applicant.',
