                'Art. 9(2)(h) permits health data processing for healthcare provision but requires suitable safeguards including professional secrecy obligations. The internal email confirms the hospital knew TriageAI had a life-threatening gap in posterior stroke recognition and took no corrective action for months. That deliberate inaction is inconsistent with suitable safeguards. Art. 22(4) then requires explicit consent or Art. 9(2) justification for automated decisions based on special category data \u2014 use ev3 to show neither the safeguards nor the justification was properly maintained.'
