        content: '<div class="doc-section"><p class="doc-section-title">StreamVault Creator Notification \u2014 Monetisation Status Change, 14 September 2024</p><p><em>Subject: Important Update Regarding Your Channel Monetisation</em></p><p>"Dear Creator, Following automated review of your content in accordance with our Creator Monetisation Policy, a policy violation has been detected. As a result, monetisation on your channel has been suspended with immediate effect. To appeal this decision, please use the Appeal function in your Creator Dashboard."</p><hr/><p class="doc-section-title">Art. 22 GDPR Analysis (annotated):</p><p><strong>Art. 22(1) \u2014 Solely automated decision with significant effects:</strong> <span class="doc-highlight">No human reviewed Lena\'s channel before demonetisation. The decision eliminated \u20AC3,000/month income. The notification does not disclose that the decision was made entirely by BrandGuard AI or that the appeal will be processed by AppealBot.</span></p><p><strong>Art. 22(3) \u2014 Right to human intervention, point of view, contest:</strong> <span class="doc-highlight">The appeal mechanism routes to AppealBot, not a human reviewer. The notification does not inform Lena of any right to human intervention. The 12-second appeal resolution is structurally incapable of genuine review.</span></p><p><strong>Art. 13(2)(f) \u2014 Logic and consequences disclosure:</strong> The notification contains no information about BrandGuard\'s scoring logic, the mental health classification, the BSS threshold, or the IAB category applied. \u201CPolicy violation detected\u201D is not meaningful information about automated decision-making logic.</p></div>'
