              legal_reasoning: 'The point-of-view argument is legally correct but secondary to the fundamental question of whether AppealBot constitutes human intervention. Addressing the adequacy of the review mechanism before establishing that human intervention is required inverts the logical order. The stronger answer establishes that Art. 22(3) requires human intervention as a threshold matter before examining whether that intervention was meaningful.'
