            judge_response: 'Counsel, AI Act compliance is enforced by market surveillance authorities under a separate regulatory architecture. Even if the recommendation algorithm is high-risk under Annex III, that does not affect TrendLoop\'s Art. 34/35 DSA obligations in these proceedings. Are you abandoning the DSA claim in favour of the AI Act?',
            legal_reasoning: 'The AI Act swap trap stated in the case brief. AI Act Annex III high-risk system obligations are enforced by market surveillance authorities under a completely separate enforcement architecture. Introducing them in DSA proceedings requires a different forum, different authority, and different legal test. More fundamentally, the DSA Art. 34/35 framework was specifically designed for VLOP recommendation system risks — it is more precisely applicable, not less, than the AI Act. This pivot loses the stronger argument.'
