            judge_response: 'Counsel, GDPR Art. 7 consent validity is enforced by data protection authorities. DSA Art. 25 addresses platform interface design obligations independently of whether GDPR consent is technically valid. Does the GDPR referral advance your Art. 25 claim before this Coordinator, or does it introduce a parallel framework with a different authority and a different legal test?',
            legal_reasoning: 'The GDPR swap trap stated in the case brief. GDPR Art. 7 consent requirements and DSA Art. 25 dark pattern prohibition are distinct legal instruments enforced by different authorities. Introducing GDPR Art. 7 in DSA proceedings dilutes the Art. 25 argument, requires referral to a DPA with different proceedings, and allows DataSphere to argue GDPR compliance while sidestepping Art. 25. The DSA Art. 25 argument is fully sufficient without importing GDPR.'
