            legal_reasoning: 'A consumer law swap error. Characterising cookie consent as a "commercial transaction" to engage the UCPD is a legal stretch — consent is a data protection mechanism, not a B2C trade transaction. The UCPD also requires proof of a transactional decision in the commercial sense. Introducing the UCPD in DSA proceedings creates a jurisdictional split, requires a different authority, and applies a weaker and less precisely applicable standard than DSA Art. 25, which was specifically designed for manipulative interface design.'
