            judge_response: 'Counsel, AI Act Art. 9 risk management system obligations apply to providers of high-risk AI systems under Annex III and are enforced by market surveillance authorities — not Digital Services Coordinators. DSA Art. 34 with its specific factors in Art. 34(2) is the complete and applicable standard for this proceeding. Does the AI Act referral advance the Art. 34 finding, or introduce a parallel claim requiring different evidence and a different authority?',
            legal_reasoning: 'The AI Act swap trap stated in the case brief. AI Act Art. 9 risk management systems are enforced by market surveillance authorities for high-risk AI systems under Annex III — not by DSCs as part of DSA proceedings. DSA Art. 34 with Art. 34(2) mandatory factors is the specific, directly applicable standard and requires no AI Act supplementation. The judge\'s rejection draws the precise distinction the case brief identifies.'
