          label: 'Art. 16(1) — User-friendly mechanism design, and Art. 16(5) — Confirmation of receipt and redress information obligations',
          feedback: 'Correct. Art. 16(1) requires mechanisms that are easy to access and user-friendly, enabling any individual to submit notices — a mechanism with an 80% failure rate due to government ID requirements, 500-word legal analysis, and 10-minute timeouts fails this standard. Art. 16(5) independently requires confirmation of receipt without undue delay and information about redress possibilities — both completely absent. The two provisions are violated independently.'
