      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Art. 6(5) Compliance Statement</div><p>SearchCo maintains fair and non-discriminatory ranking practices. The Shopping Box represents a universal search feature analogous to images, maps, and news verticals, not a comparison shopping service competing with third-party aggregators.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Ranking Methodology</div><p>All services, including SearchCo Shopping, are subject to the same objective relevance algorithms. No manual intervention or preferential treatment occurs. Organic results reflect the best available content based on quality signals including price accuracy, merchant coverage, and user satisfaction.</p></div><div class="doc-highlight"><strong>Auditor Note:</strong> SearchCo claims Shopping Box is "just another search feature" and denies differential treatment in indexing. However, technical analysis (Ev2) contradicts claims of algorithmic parity.</div>'
