      title: 'Founder Affidavit — CraftGoods Ltd',
      date: 'March 10, 2028',
      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Company Background</div><p>CraftGoods is a UK-based artisanal home goods manufacturer employing 45 people. We have sold exclusively through MegaMart since 2019, generating €2.4M annually in gross merchandise value.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Ranking Displacement</div><p>In January 2026, MegaMart launched "MegaMart Basics" private-label home goods. Despite our "Handcrafted Ceramic Vase" having a 4.8-star rating (2,000 reviews) at €24.99, the search result for "ceramic vase" places MegaMart Basics\' 4.2-star product (50 reviews) at position 1 with a "Best Value" badge, while we appear on page 3. Their product costs €29.99.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Economic Impact</div><p>Our sales have declined 40% since January 2026 despite maintaining perfect seller metrics. We cannot reduce prices further without operating at a loss, while MegaMart subsidizes its private-label pricing with marketplace fee revenue.</p></div>'
