      date: 'February 28, 2028',
      content: '<div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Methodology</div><p>Analysis conducted on MegaMart\'s search API responses and frontend ranking data across 500 product queries in home goods categories.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><div class="doc-section-title">Key Findings</div><p>1. <strong>House Brand Boost Parameter:</strong> The algorithm contains a hard-coded variable "houseBrandBoost" set to +35% applied exclusively to products where sellerID = "MegaMart_Private_Label".</p><p>2. <strong>Badge Allocation:</strong> "Best Value" and "Recommended" badges are automatically assigned to MegaMart Basics products when they appear in top 10 results, regardless of price competitiveness vs third-party alternatives.</p><p>3. <strong>Quality Signal Override:</strong> The +35% boost overrides standard quality signals including review velocity, rating averages, and price competitiveness scores in the ranking calculation.</p></div>'
