            text: 'Your Honour, opposing counsel\'s quality defense is legally inadmissible. Article 6(5) establishes a per se prohibition on self-preferencing in ranking. The text contains no exception for "quality-verified" products or consumer protection benefits. The DMA\'s architecture distinguishes between prohibited practices (Art. 5) and high-risk systems (Art. 6) where compliance measures might apply. Art. 6(5) falls within the prohibited conduct category that admits no efficiency, quality, or consumer benefit defenses. MegaMart\'s +35% boost is unlawful regardless of its supply chain controls. The regulation prioritizes contestability and fairness over subjective quality judgments by gatekeepers.',
