          questionText: 'Your own Legal team stated in the presentation that the Privacy Policy click-through \'does not constitute specific choice under Art. 4(11) GDPR as incorporated by Art. 5(2) DMA,\' and that the all-or-nothing deletion opt-out \'does not constitute a genuine less personalised alternative.\' Those are your lawyers\' conclusions, not a matter of external interpretation. Did OmniTech implement any changes to its consent mechanism following Legal\'s assessment?',
          witnessResponse: 'We have been engaged in ongoing compliance work. The implementation of consent changes is a complex engineering and product challenge that requires careful design.',
          followUpImpact: 'positive'
