              'Art. 5(6) DMA protects raising issues about \'any practice of the gatekeeper.\' Commission rate increases are a practice of RideApp. Does a non-disparagement clause that prevents public criticism of the commission rate restrict the ability to raise issues about that practice, even if it does not directly prohibit authority contact?'
